{
  "texts": [
    "The data from online encyclopedia websites is written and edited by experts, volunteers, or community contributors, providing a certain level of authority and reliability.",
    "Due to its ease of accessibility, it is included at a higher frequency in pre-training corpora, serving as a cornerstone in enhancing the knowledge base of LLMs.",
    "The most common encyclopedia corpus is Wikipedia foot_18.",
    "It possesses characteristics such as being free, open-source, multilingual, and having high textual value.",
    "Frequently, specific language data from Wikipedia is selected, crawled, and filtered to serve as part of the pre-training corpus."
  ]
}